/reports/*
  X-Robots-Tag: noindex, nofollow

# Self-hosted woff2 files are content-addressed by filename and never
# rewritten, so cache them aggressively at the browser AND CF edge.
/fonts/*.woff2
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
  Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *

# Images use fixed (non-hashed) filenames, so we can't mark them immutable. The
# 1-day TTL we started with was flagged by BOTH GTmetrix ("serve static assets with
# an efficient cache policy", 24h) and Pingdom ("add Expires headers"), and the hero
# has now settled, so raise it to 30 days. Repeat visits and the edge cache both hold
# far longer, which is what those audits want.
# ⚠️ Trade-off: a replaced image keeps serving from cache for up to 30 days. If you
# swap an image, either rename it or append a ?v= query in the HTML to bust it —
# do NOT rely on the TTL expiring.
/images/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=2592000

# HTML edge-caching (2026-07-18). The page HTML was measuring cf-cache-status:
# DYNAMIC — Cloudflare decides cache eligibility by FILE EXTENSION, not MIME type, so
# an extensionless URL like /prenatal-massage-calgary/ is passed to origin on EVERY
# request. That origin round-trip is a large part of TTFB (638ms measured), and TTFB
# directly gates FCP and LCP — the two metrics still red on PSI.
#
# Safe to cache here: this page is fully static (no server-side personalization; the
# splitter in functions/_lib/split.js only touches /massage-therapy-calgary, and
# UTM/gclid are read client-side by utm-capture.js).
#
#   max-age=0             -> browsers always revalidate, so a visitor never sees stale
#   s-maxage=600          -> the EDGE serves it for 10 min without touching origin
#   stale-while-revalidate-> edge can serve instantly while refreshing in background
#
# Deliberately a SHORT edge TTL: this is the live ad funnel, so a bad deploy must not
# stick. If a deploy needs to go out instantly, purge the Cloudflare cache.
# NOTE: if this doesn't flip cf-cache-status off DYNAMIC, Cloudflare Pages is ignoring
# it and it needs a dashboard Cache Rule (Cache eligibility: eligible) instead.
/prenatal-massage-calgary/
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, s-maxage=600, stale-while-revalidate=86400
/prenatal-massage-calgary/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, s-maxage=600, stale-while-revalidate=86400
